v></header><header class=\"section_team-profile-large_header-1\"><div class=\"padding-global\"><div class=\"container-large\"><div class=\"padding-section-large\"><div class=\"team-profile-large_header-1_component\"><div class=\"w-layout-grid team-profile-large_header-1_content\"><div class=\"team-profile-large_header-1_content-left\"><h2>Our expertise covers</h2></div><div class=\"team-profile-large_header-1_content-right\"><div class=\"w-richtext\"><h4>Telecom leases and renewals</h4><p>• Negotiating telecom leases</p><p>• Lease renewals under the Electronic Communications Code</p><p>• Landlord and Tenant Act 1954 advice</p><p>• Rent reviews and compensation claims</p><p>‍</p><h4>Development and site removal</h4><p>• Redevelopment strategy where telecom apparatus is present</p><p>• Removal or relocation of telecom masts and equipment</p><p>• Vacant possession advice</p><p>• Managing redevelopment alongside telecom operators</p><p>‍</p><h4>Site access, upgrades and sharing</h4><p>• Multi Skilled Visit survey access requests</p><p>• 5G upgrades and equipment installation</p><p>• Site sharing with other telecom networks</p><p>• Negotiating controlled access rights</p><p>‍</p><h4>Breaches of lease and rent disputes</h4><p>• Unpaid rent and service charge disputes</p><p>• Breach of telecom lease terms</p><p>• Unauthorised site sharing or equipment installation</p><p>• Enforcement of telecom lease obligations</p><p>‍</p><h4>Dilapidations and site restoration</h4><p>• Telecom dilapidations disputes</p><p>• Removal of redundant telecom infrastructure</p><p>• Structural damage claims</p><p>• Recovery of repair costs and compensation</p><p>‍</p><h4>Wayleave agreements</h4><p>• Negotiating telecom wayleave agreements</p><p>• Access and maintenance obligations</p><p>• Protecting redevelopment potential</p><p>• Limiting long term restrictions on land use</p><p>‍</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></header><div class=\"section_signposts\"><div class=\"padding-global\"